    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1964-03-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1964-03-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="327"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d327">
                <head>327. Memorandum From Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_RD1" type="from"
                        >Rusk</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_JLB1" type="to"
                        >Johnson</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d327fn1">Source: <persName>Johnson</persName>
                        Library, National Security File, Country File, Haiti, Vol. II.
                        Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1964-03-24">March 24, 1964</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Haitian Request for U.S. Grant Assistance</item>
                </list>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="italic">Recommended Action</hi>
                </p>
                <p>I recommend you authorize Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_TBEL1"
                        >Timmons</persName> to inform President Duvalier that you have personally
                    approved the decision not to accede to his request for grant budget-supporting
                        assistance.<note n="2" xml:id="d327fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_SRM1">Sayre</persName> indicated that President
                            <persName corresp="#p_JLB1">Johnson</persName> disapproved the action on
                        March 26.</note>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="italic">Discussion</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_TBEL1">Timmons</persName> has made excellent
                    progress in establishing the productive relations with Haiti that our own
                    self-interests require. President Duvalier has seized upon this favorable
                    evolution to request budget-supporting assistance as “evidence of the
                    genuineness of U.S. goodwill toward his Government.” Although some such aid may
                    have to be given later, we do not believe we should do so now.</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Duvalier is an extreme egocentric and believes that if he
                        could only “get through” to you personally, you would grant all his
                        requests. It is thus important for Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_TBEL1"
                            >Timmons</persName> to be able to say that the U.S. response has your
                        personal approval.</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Since January we have taken a number of actions favorable to Haitiʼs interests.
                    We are now encouraging tourism to Haiti, processing investment guarantee
                    applications and supporting <gloss target="#t_IDB1">IDB</gloss> loans to Haiti
                    that meet the Bankʼs criteria.</p>
                <p>Continuation of the productive dialogue already begun may require us to be
                    additionally forthcoming. At the same time, we need <pb facs="0804" n="769"
                        xml:id="pg_769"/> persuasive arguments in pressing the Haitian government to
                    pay off its debts. To serve both purposes, we plan to explore, without
                    commitment, the reinstatement of the 1962 Port-au-Prince airport loan ($2.8
                    million) which was cancelled in 1963 as a consequence of Haitian defaults on
                    previous U.S. loans.<note n="3" xml:id="d327fn3">A handwritten note at the end
                        of the memorandum reads: “This is <persName corresp="#p_MTC1">Tom
                            Mann</persName>ʼs recommendation.”</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RD1">
                            <hi rend="strong">DR</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
